The normalizer in `bb004_mdtable/normalizer.py:1` detects pipe-table blocks (consecutive `|`-leading lines whose second row is a separator), computes per-column widths from header+data cells, then re-emits each row with `| cell-padded |` formatting and normalizes every separator cell to `---`. Non-table lines pass through untouched, and the output is idempotent since re-normalizing yields identical widths and cells.
